
[1]shrew

   SHREW, n.

   1. A peevish, brawling, turbulent, vexatious woman. It appears to have
   originally been applied to males as well as females; but is now
   restricted to the latter.

   The man had got a shrew for his wife, and there could be no quiet in
   the house with her. L'Estrange.

   2. A shrew-mouse.

   SHREW, v.t. To beshrew; to curse. Obs.
